{"word":"πατρίς","slug":"πατρίς","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>πατρίς, ίδος, ἡ</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:πατήρ\">πατήρ</a></el>] ‘a place or region one can call home’<b><p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>a.</pp></b> in sense of native land, <b>homeland <a href='B:500 4:44'>J 4:44</a>;</b> in imagery <b><a href='B:650 11:14'>Hb 11:14</a>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>b.</pp></b> in narrower sense <b>home area, hometown <a href='B:470 13:54'>Mt 13:54</a>, <a href='B:470 13:57'>57</a>; <a href='B:480 6:1'>Mk 6:1</a>, <a href='B:480 6:4'>4</a>; <a href='B:490 4:23'>Lk 4:23f</a>; <a href='B:510 18:27'>Ac 18:27</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ v.l.\">v.l.</a></b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:πατρικός\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:Πατροβᾶς\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}